    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-19T02:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-19T02:35:00-05:00" n="637"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d637">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">391.1164/144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-19T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >July 19, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>171. Legation’s 164, July 16. Under Secretary of Foreign Affairs has informed the
                    representatives that subject to the approval of the Council of Ministers he
                    accepted that payments be spread over 3 years and suggested that a first payment
                    of $100,000 be made in September 1940 and 200,000 by next March. Thereafter
                    300,000 1941, 1942 and 1943. Interest at 8 percent on all installments not paid
                    on date due. Representatives have agreed in principle.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
